<topic id="xml-transformation-with-xslt">
  <title>XML Transformation with XSLT</title>
  <shortdesc>This type of transformation specifies the transformation parameters and location of an
    XSLT stylesheet that is applied to the edited XML document. This scenario is useful when you
    develop an XML document and the XSLT document is in its final form.</shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>XML with XSLT</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>New<indexterm>XML with
            XSLT</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>XML transformation with XSLT</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To create an <uicontrol>XML transformation with XSLT</uicontrol> scenario, use one of the
      following methods:<ul>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png" id="image_b25_vvv_sr"/>
            Configure Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_c_shortcut"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_tc_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
          toolbar or the <menucascade product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>XML transformation with XSLT</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/ApplyStyleSheet16.png" id="image_acl_5yv_sr"/>
            Apply Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_t_shortcut"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_tt_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
          toolbar or the <menucascade product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>XML transformation with XSLT</uicontrol>.<note
            conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/note-001"/></li>
        <li>Go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and select <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"
              id="image_ikn_vvv_sr"/> Transformation Scenarios</uicontrol> to display <xref
            href="scenarios-view.dita#scenarios-view">this view</xref>. Click the
            <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select <uicontrol>XML transformation with
            XSLT</uicontrol>.</li>
      </ul></p>
    <p>All three methods open the <uicontrol>New Scenario</uicontrol> dialog box.</p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/name-storage-options"
      product="author developer editor"/>
    <p product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">The upper part of the dialog box
      allows you to specify the <uicontrol>Name</uicontrol> of the transformation scenario.</p>
    <p>The lower part of the dialog box contains several tabs that allow you to configure the
      options that control the transformation.</p>
  </body>
</topic>
